    • Method Detail

      • getDefaultMetaObject

        public static <T> com.mysema.query.types.EntityPath<T> getDefaultMetaObject(Class<T> entityType)
        Get the default meta-object of Entity class.

        The meta-classes must be generated with default options:

        • The same package that the Entity type;
        • The name of meta-class must be have the default target name, beginning by Q.
          For example if the name is mypackage.MyClass, the meta-class must be mypackage.QMyClass.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The Entity type.
        Parameters:
        entityType - The Entity type.
        Returns:
        The EntityPathBase corresponding.
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - Meta-class not found from Entity.
        UnsupportedOperationException - Error during getting default meta-instance.
